                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>Wednesday, 18th Aug</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear. <addressee>Mr. Leeser.</addressee></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yesterday I forwarded an article for<lb/> your approval &amp;c and I\n                remember now that in the<lb/> Hurry of copying the last part I omitted to give the\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">notes</hi><lb/> I enclose them. You can give what I send to\n                the<lb/> printer instead of the original page. The note about<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Laws of Divorce</hi> I think will apply to <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                        ><persName>Sim Abraham</persName></hi><lb/> last week, <persName>Mrs.\n                    Motta</persName> gave me some Spanish books<lb/> belonging to old <persName>Mr\n                        Aziredo<add>?</add></persName>, among them is the<lb/> “Hoboth Hallebaboth”\n                also in Spanish and in looking<lb/> over it I found this passage. I referred to\n                    <persName>Dr. E.</persName> who<lb/> has a copy in Hebrew and between us you\n                have a<lb/> “note” which strengthens the position you took in the<lb/>\n                <placeName>Cleveland</placeName> affair without saving you the <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >trouble</hi> to answer him. If you have not a copy in Hebrew<lb/> and\n                    <del>want</del> can use this one in Spanish. I will <hi rend=\"underline\">give\n                    it</hi> to<lb/> you. I also can supply you with a sett of\n                        <date><sic>Rorsanna</sic></date><add>?</add><lb/> &amp; <date>kippur</date>\n                and daily prayers (A Hazans copy with prayers for the whole<lb/> year) also in\n                Spanish. As I have three or four setts.<lb/> Shall I send them if I can find a\n                    <sic>covenent</sic> oppty?<lb/> I have also two copies of the Pentateuch in\n                Spanish with copious notes in Hebrew<lb/> from <hi rend=\"underline\">all the learned\n                    sciences</hi><add>?</add>. Will you have <hi rend=\"underline\">one</hi>? <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">one</hi> copy is enough<lb/> for me.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have not seen the sheet of your bible sent to <persName>M\n                        Serin<add>?</add></persName><lb/> he is a little hurt I think that you have\n                not written to him If<lb/> you can spare time. you might write him a few lines<lb/>\n                my wife is not very well. She sends her kind regards. <persName>Mrs<lb/>\n                    Motta</persName> tells me she has some money to send you and promised it</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3n58d31f/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
